SETUP
Created virtual environment [py_env]
    > python -m venv djangoEnv

Activate virtual environment
    > py_env\Scripts\activate
        WINDOWS SPECIFIC
            Scripts disabled on my system
            Windows Powershell Command (Running as Administrator)
                $ Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted
                https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/microsoft.powershell.core/about/about_execution_policies?view=powershell-7.2
        Allow the activate script execute

Install Django and Pin Our Dependencies
    > python -m pip install django
    > python -m pip install djangorestframework
    > python -m pip install django-cors-headers
    > python -m pip freeze > py_requirements.txt
        Pin the dependencies & django version into requirements.txt

Create a Django Project [team_builder_django]
    Django PROJECTS are the larger-level unit
    Django APPLICATIONS are are the lower-level unit
    A Django PROJECT can have many Django APPLICATIONS
    > django-admin startproject team_builder_django

Start a Django App
    Django APP folder will be where most of of the development occurs
    Created the single CORE application WITHIN the project
    > cd team_builder_django
    > python manage.py startapp core

DEV LOG
    core
        admin.py
            Registered Employee as having an admin interface
        models.py  
            Created Employee model
        serializer.py
            Serializes the Employee model to native Python datatypes (Might not be necessary?)
        views.py 
            -Added a class for React REST API 

    team_builder_django
        urls.py
            Added a path() to include() ReactView
        settings.py
            Add to INSTALLED APPS   
                'rest_framework', 
                'core', 
                'corsheaders'
            Add to MIDDLEWARE
                'corsheaders.middleware.CorsMiddleware'
            Add new dictionary REST_FRAMEWORK{}
                'DEFAULT_PERMISSION_CLASSES': ['rest_framework.permissions.AllowAny']
            Add new variable CORS_ORIGIN_ALLOW_ALL = True
            Set TIMEZONE to 'America/Chicago' (from UTC)
