DJANGO NOTES
Documentation Notes
    Files
        manage.py
            Important file, invoked for most django execution
        models.py  
            Database layouts + additional metadata
        settings.py
            Project settings
            Project reference errors are often created here :(
            Database credentials / references

    Functions
    path()
        Has four arguments; 
        2 required
            route : str that contains an urlpattern
            view  : ???
        2 optional
            kwargs: {} arbitrary arguments
            name  : used for django references (templates)
            
Common Django Commands
    > python manage.py runserver
        Runs the development server using manage.py
    > python manage.py runserver 8080
        Runs server on port 8080
    > python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0:8000
        Runs server at IP 0.0.0.0 and PORT 8000
    > python manage.py makemigrations <app_name>
        PREPARES changes to the MODELS (e.g. the database format) to application
    > python manage.py migrate
        TODO: Verify this#
        COMMITS changes to the MODELS
            Necessary after adding changes to do before running the server

